1
00:00:47,777 --> 00:00:51,072
THE APARTMENT JOB

2
00:00:53,157 --> 00:00:56,244
Let's do a solo shot
of the eldest son this time.

3
00:01:00,790 --> 00:01:04,085
You already look so good.

4
00:01:04,169 --> 00:01:05,837
I'll start shooting now.

5
00:01:05,920 --> 00:01:08,006
One, two, three.

6
00:01:08,089 --> 00:01:09,507
Hello.

7
00:01:09,591 --> 00:01:10,800
You scared me.

8
00:01:11,634 --> 00:01:13,761
You almost burst my eardrums,
you little brat.

9
00:01:13,845 --> 00:01:15,388
One, two, three!

10
00:01:16,222 --> 00:01:19,058
That's great. You look so reliable.

11
00:01:19,142 --> 00:01:21,019
Can you smile a little?

12
00:01:21,102 --> 00:01:22,395
All right. One more shot.

13
00:01:22,478 --> 00:01:24,022
One, two, three!

14
00:01:24,105 --> 00:01:24,939
Nice.

15
00:01:26,316 --> 00:01:27,859
Stop playing with that.

16
00:01:30,403 --> 00:01:33,656
-I'm tired. Stop it.
-Hello!

17
00:01:33,740 --> 00:01:36,284
-Hello.
-Stop.

18
00:01:40,038 --> 00:01:40,955
I'm going to win.

19
00:01:41,664 --> 00:01:43,249
I'll win, no matter what.

20
00:01:43,333 --> 00:01:46,961
I'll win and save Yong-man
and protect my guys.

21
00:01:47,587 --> 00:01:48,671
I'll make sure of it.

22
00:01:51,090 --> 00:01:52,717
Here's our contract. Read it and sign it.

23
00:01:54,636 --> 00:01:56,554
You didn't need to write up a contract.

24
00:01:58,806 --> 00:02:00,475
The photoshoot took way too long.

25
00:02:01,893 --> 00:02:04,479
You should've at least given me food.
I've been starving…

26
00:02:04,562 --> 00:02:07,273
Stop grumbling.
You're going to enjoy the food anyway.

27
00:02:07,357 --> 00:02:08,191
Eat up.

28
00:02:09,108 --> 00:02:10,235
Excuse me.

29
00:02:10,318 --> 00:02:12,070
"A penalty three times the amount issued

30
00:02:12,153 --> 00:02:13,863
for termination due to Party B's fault?"

31
00:02:15,031 --> 00:02:17,408
What could I possibly be at fault for?

32
00:02:18,284 --> 00:02:21,746
If the contract ever has to be terminated,
it would be your fault.

33
00:02:21,829 --> 00:02:24,916
I'm a professional when it comes to work.

34
00:02:25,583 --> 00:02:28,628
So unfortunately,
we're going to have to cancel this.

35
00:02:28,711 --> 00:02:30,797
If you do your job professionally,
there won't be…

36
00:02:31,589 --> 00:02:33,675
-Remove that clause.
-Yes, sir.

37
00:02:37,512 --> 00:02:39,264
Have you been to the rooftop?

38
00:02:39,347 --> 00:02:40,181
Hey, be quiet.

39
00:02:40,265 --> 00:02:43,017
I had to go to the rooftop
to get that clause removed.

40
00:02:43,101 --> 00:02:45,019
Your soup will get cold.
Just sign it and eat.

41
00:02:47,146 --> 00:02:48,648
KANG HA-RI

42
00:02:50,358 --> 00:02:52,110
It looks like a celebrity autograph.

43
00:02:52,735 --> 00:02:54,237
All done, right?

44
00:02:54,320 --> 00:02:55,154
Mr. Park.

45
00:02:55,905 --> 00:02:58,574
I believe our meeting like this
can be called fate.

46
00:02:58,658 --> 00:03:01,285
They say people who live together
and eat together

47
00:03:01,369 --> 00:03:02,578
are a family…

48
00:03:02,662 --> 00:03:04,080
Shut it.

49
00:03:04,163 --> 00:03:05,957
Goodness. Excuse me.

50
00:03:06,040 --> 00:03:08,167
You shouldn't say that to your elders.

51
00:03:09,085 --> 00:03:11,629
You keep calling him "excuse me."
He's Mr. Park.

52
00:03:14,007 --> 00:03:14,882
Let's sort this out.

53
00:03:15,842 --> 00:03:18,011
She's your sister-in-law now.
Call her Ms. Kang.

54
00:03:18,094 --> 00:03:19,429
-Ms. Kang.
-Ms. Kang.

55
00:03:21,014 --> 00:03:22,849
-And the Lizard…
-Lizard?

56
00:03:22,932 --> 00:03:24,058
Ha-ri, my daughter-in-law.

57
00:03:25,018 --> 00:03:27,186
-Gyeong-buk.
-Mom!

58
00:03:29,897 --> 00:03:31,482
And I'll call you "darling."

59
00:03:33,067 --> 00:03:34,736
I'm getting goosebumps.

60
00:03:34,819 --> 00:03:37,030
How about just "honey"?

61
00:03:37,113 --> 00:03:38,740
Fine by me.

62
00:03:38,823 --> 00:03:40,575
Call my guys by their last name too.

63
00:03:40,658 --> 00:03:41,868
What?

64
00:03:43,119 --> 00:03:46,956
This whole honorifics thing
in Korea is ridiculous.

65
00:03:47,040 --> 00:03:50,168
They're supposed to be
my husband's younger brothers.

66
00:03:50,251 --> 00:03:52,754
Didn't you say you're a professional?

67
00:03:55,089 --> 00:03:57,759
Mr. Kim, Mr. Jang, Mr. Kim.

68
00:03:59,677 --> 00:04:00,720
Happy?

69
00:04:01,554 --> 00:04:03,473
-Let's eat.
-Yes, sir.

70
00:04:04,057 --> 00:04:06,309
Shouldn't they address you properly too?

71
00:04:06,392 --> 00:04:08,728
You're their older brother now.

72
00:04:08,811 --> 00:04:09,771
Aren't you brothers?

73
00:04:11,064 --> 00:04:12,106
Right. It's been a while.

74
00:04:12,815 --> 00:04:14,609
Treat me like your older brother now.

75
00:04:15,735 --> 00:04:16,611
Really?

76
00:04:17,779 --> 00:04:18,613
Hae-kang.

77
00:04:18,696 --> 00:04:20,365
Okay, Hae-kang.

78
00:04:31,876 --> 00:04:33,086
Sorry.

79
00:04:33,169 --> 00:04:34,045
Just eat.

80
00:04:34,128 --> 00:04:37,131
No. I made a promise to myself.

81
00:04:37,215 --> 00:04:38,466
He said he's on a diet.

82
00:04:38,549 --> 00:04:40,426
Something called
"intermittent fasting," sir.

83
00:04:40,510 --> 00:04:41,511
I mean, Hae-kang.

84
00:04:42,095 --> 00:04:43,679
Intermittent what?

85
00:04:44,972 --> 00:04:46,057
Intermittent fasting.

86
00:04:46,140 --> 00:04:49,685
I fast for 16 hours a day

87
00:04:49,769 --> 00:04:52,647
and eat freely in the remaining hours.

88
00:04:52,730 --> 00:04:54,774
But it's fasting time right now.

89
00:04:54,857 --> 00:04:56,484
Then why are you adding salt and pepper?

90
00:04:56,567 --> 00:04:57,902
I just want the feel of it.

91
00:04:59,195 --> 00:05:00,571
Let's be an intermittent family.

92
00:05:01,489 --> 00:05:02,740
Whenever it's necessary,

93
00:05:02,824 --> 00:05:05,576
we'll be a mom, dad, child,
uncle, and nephew for each other.

94
00:05:06,285 --> 00:05:07,912
And let's call this project

95
00:05:07,995 --> 00:05:10,665
the "Intermittent Family Project."

96
00:05:14,627 --> 00:05:15,628
Thanks to me!

97
00:05:16,462 --> 00:05:18,172
What a great idea.

98
00:05:18,256 --> 00:05:19,424
Intermittent family?

99
00:05:19,507 --> 00:05:20,967
-That's perfect. Stop that.
-Clap.

100
00:05:21,050 --> 00:05:22,468
Give him a round of applause.

101
00:05:25,680 --> 00:05:27,849
Sit down. Father!

102
00:05:28,766 --> 00:05:30,309
How did you come up with that?

103
00:05:30,393 --> 00:05:31,769
-Are you okay?
-Cheers to that!

104
00:05:32,478 --> 00:05:37,150
THE APARTMENT JOB

105
00:05:47,702 --> 00:05:49,120
I'm just handing in the form today.

106
00:05:49,203 --> 00:05:51,330
You can come to our house
starting tomorrow.

107
00:05:51,414 --> 00:05:52,915
What form?

108
00:05:54,792 --> 00:05:55,626
Wait! Stop!

109
00:05:57,670 --> 00:06:00,006
True Value State? Your house is here?

110
00:06:00,089 --> 00:06:01,299
Is there a problem?

111
00:06:02,133 --> 00:06:04,218
Why didn't you tell me
your place was True Value?

112
00:06:04,302 --> 00:06:05,428
Then I would've refused.

113
00:06:06,053 --> 00:06:09,140
Why? Does someone you know live here?

114
00:06:09,223 --> 00:06:10,683
My sis…

115
00:06:12,977 --> 00:06:14,812
Anyway, I can't do this.

116
00:06:17,356 --> 00:06:19,692
Is this why you wanted
that penalty clause removed?

117
00:06:32,079 --> 00:06:33,706
Please pick up.

118
00:06:35,374 --> 00:06:38,252
Hey, Ha-jeong. Where are you?

119
00:06:39,295 --> 00:06:42,465
I just enrolled in classes.

120
00:06:42,548 --> 00:06:44,217
-Why?
-It's nothing.

121
00:06:44,926 --> 00:06:46,844
So you're not at work today?

122
00:06:46,928 --> 00:06:49,096
Work? I took the day off.

123
00:06:50,640 --> 00:06:52,016
Still not done?

124
00:06:53,100 --> 00:06:55,603
It's nothing. See you later.

125
00:06:57,104 --> 00:06:58,648
Thank you.

126
00:07:06,739 --> 00:07:08,241
How may I help you?

127
00:07:09,992 --> 00:07:13,204
You're the one who took care of that guy
blocking the parking lot.

128
00:07:13,287 --> 00:07:16,040
Things were so hectic then,
I didn't get to greet you properly.

129
00:07:16,123 --> 00:07:18,292
I'm Choi Yeong-jae, the facility manager.

130
00:07:20,169 --> 00:07:21,504
I'm Park Hae-kang.

131
00:07:21,587 --> 00:07:22,505
Nice to meet you.

132
00:07:24,215 --> 00:07:25,383
How is the parking situation?

133
00:07:26,384 --> 00:07:29,845
He parks perfectly within the lines now.

134
00:07:30,471 --> 00:07:31,389
That's great.

135
00:07:32,390 --> 00:07:34,850
Hey, why are we even here?

136
00:07:34,934 --> 00:07:37,770
Ms. Kang,
it's intermittent family time right now.

137
00:07:38,437 --> 00:07:39,480
Ha-ri.

138
00:07:41,065 --> 00:07:43,234
Mr. Kim, why are we here?

139
00:07:43,317 --> 00:07:46,320
We're here to submit
the building rep application form,

140
00:07:46,404 --> 00:07:47,989
Ms. Kang.

141
00:07:48,072 --> 00:07:49,240
Building rep?

142
00:07:49,323 --> 00:07:51,784
This is my building representative
application form.

143
00:07:53,619 --> 00:07:54,829
You're running for building rep?

144
00:07:57,248 --> 00:07:58,541
Your photo looks great.

145
00:07:59,166 --> 00:08:00,585
Yun-seo, register this.

146
00:08:00,668 --> 00:08:01,919
Yes, sir.

147
00:08:02,003 --> 00:08:03,713
Who are the other…

148
00:08:04,797 --> 00:08:06,382
This is my family.

149
00:08:08,467 --> 00:08:09,844
Hello.

150
00:08:12,430 --> 00:08:14,640
My goodness.

151
00:08:15,349 --> 00:08:18,394
You seem like a very close-knit family.

152
00:08:19,312 --> 00:08:22,732
You could've just applied online,

153
00:08:22,815 --> 00:08:25,901
but you brought your entire family along.
That's quite rare.

154
00:08:26,652 --> 00:08:30,698
That's right. It's rare to see
such a close-knit family these days.

155
00:08:32,533 --> 00:08:33,492
This is my wife.

156
00:08:34,368 --> 00:08:35,328
Isn't she beautiful?

157
00:08:36,412 --> 00:08:38,080
And my son is very bright.

158
00:08:38,164 --> 00:08:40,833
He's a great son too.

159
00:08:40,916 --> 00:08:41,876
Nice to meet you.

160
00:08:41,959 --> 00:08:44,670
And my father here used to be an artist.

161
00:08:46,547 --> 00:08:48,132
These three are my younger brothers.

162
00:08:48,215 --> 00:08:49,342
-Hello!
-Hello!

163
00:08:50,426 --> 00:08:52,386
We're a very happy family.

164
00:08:53,596 --> 00:08:55,097
Stay healthy, Father!

165
00:08:56,015 --> 00:08:57,642
A very close-knit family!

166
00:08:59,435 --> 00:09:00,978
-Very close brothers!
-Very close brothers!

167
00:09:01,062 --> 00:09:03,439
Then is my building rep
candidate registration

168
00:09:03,522 --> 00:09:05,066
complete now?

169
00:09:05,149 --> 00:09:06,150
Yes.

170
00:09:06,233 --> 00:09:11,238
It'll be officially announced
in District 4 tomorrow morning.

171
00:09:12,531 --> 00:09:13,532
District 4.

172
00:09:15,326 --> 00:09:16,327
We'll do our best!

173
00:09:17,912 --> 00:09:21,165
Why do I have to pay
20,000 won every month

174
00:09:21,248 --> 00:09:23,376
for a gym that I never even use?

175
00:09:23,459 --> 00:09:24,669
This is ridiculous.

176
00:09:24,752 --> 00:09:26,253
-Hello.
-Hello.

177
00:09:26,337 --> 00:09:27,797
Hello.

178
00:09:29,632 --> 00:09:30,800
Mr. Choi!

179
00:09:30,883 --> 00:09:33,052
Mr. Choi, come out here!

180
00:09:33,135 --> 00:09:34,887
Hello, ma'am.

181
00:09:34,970 --> 00:09:36,389
What brings you here today?

182
00:09:37,014 --> 00:09:40,017
Mr. Choi, I told you last time

183
00:09:40,101 --> 00:09:42,269
that I don't use the gym, sauna,

184
00:09:42,353 --> 00:09:44,563
and breakfast services here.

185
00:09:44,647 --> 00:09:47,191
Why should I pay 20,000 won
every month for them?

186
00:09:47,274 --> 00:09:49,068
That's nonsense.

187
00:09:49,151 --> 00:09:51,946
And I told you last time
that the 20,000 won

188
00:09:52,029 --> 00:09:55,408
is a shared maintenance cost
for those services and facilities,

189
00:09:55,491 --> 00:09:58,536
so every household in this complex
is required to pay it.

190
00:09:58,619 --> 00:10:00,621
Why should people who never use them

191
00:10:00,705 --> 00:10:04,750
pay the same amount
as people who use them 30 times a month?

192
00:10:04,834 --> 00:10:08,379
You can ask anyone passing by
if that makes any sense.

193
00:10:08,462 --> 00:10:11,090
Don't you agree? Am I wrong?

194
00:10:12,049 --> 00:10:13,134
Goodness.

195
00:10:13,801 --> 00:10:15,219
-Pardon?
-You're the guy

196
00:10:15,302 --> 00:10:18,723
who hit that car
in front of the parking lot last time.

197
00:10:18,806 --> 00:10:20,015
Hello.

198
00:10:20,599 --> 00:10:21,559
Right.

199
00:10:25,688 --> 00:10:26,772
I'm Park Hae-kang.

200
00:10:27,398 --> 00:10:29,066
I'm Jang Suk-jin.

201
00:10:29,150 --> 00:10:30,568
Seeing you up close,

202
00:10:31,485 --> 00:10:32,987
you're quite handsome.

203
00:10:34,739 --> 00:10:36,574
He's my eldest son.

204
00:10:36,657 --> 00:10:39,243
But what brings you here?

205
00:10:39,326 --> 00:10:41,954
Why would you ask him that?

206
00:10:42,037 --> 00:10:45,916
I should know everything going on
in my apartment complex.

207
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:47,793
I need to be aware of everything.

208
00:10:47,877 --> 00:10:49,837
What are they doing here?

209
00:10:49,920 --> 00:10:52,006
He's running for building representative.

210
00:10:52,089 --> 00:10:53,340
Really?

211
00:10:54,216 --> 00:10:55,426
Building representative?

212
00:10:56,135 --> 00:10:58,763
I see.

213
00:10:59,597 --> 00:11:00,723
And these folks are…

214
00:11:02,391 --> 00:11:04,477
This is my close-knit family.

215
00:11:05,394 --> 00:11:06,687
-Hello, ma'am.
-Hello, ma'am.

216
00:11:06,771 --> 00:11:08,481
Bonjour, charming lady.

217
00:11:09,648 --> 00:11:10,483
Your family?

218
00:11:12,234 --> 00:11:13,068
Goodness me.

219
00:11:15,029 --> 00:11:20,493
There's no way I'd forget people
who stand out this much.

220
00:11:20,576 --> 00:11:22,870
So you all

221
00:11:22,953 --> 00:11:24,997
are actually a family?

222
00:11:25,080 --> 00:11:26,290
Ma'am.

223
00:11:26,874 --> 00:11:28,417
They just said they're a family.

224
00:11:28,501 --> 00:11:30,628
Why would they lie about being a family?

225
00:11:30,711 --> 00:11:31,712
I just meant…

226
00:11:32,963 --> 00:11:36,800
I'm the eyes and ears of True Value State.

227
00:11:36,884 --> 00:11:40,221
But strangely,
I've never seen these people before, so--

228
00:11:40,304 --> 00:11:44,183
Ms. Jang, if your business here is done,
why don't you leave…

229
00:11:46,227 --> 00:11:49,188
Right. How strange.

230
00:11:49,939 --> 00:11:50,898
-Strange…
-Mr. Choi.

231
00:11:50,981 --> 00:11:53,359
-Yes?
-Did you check?

232
00:11:54,068 --> 00:11:55,152
Check what?

233
00:11:55,236 --> 00:11:57,363
You know,

234
00:11:57,446 --> 00:11:59,323
my application
for building representative.

235
00:11:59,406 --> 00:12:02,493
I applied online ages ago.

236
00:12:05,955 --> 00:12:07,373
Right, everyone.

237
00:12:07,456 --> 00:12:11,210
Let's all make True Value
a great apartment complex.

238
00:12:11,293 --> 00:12:13,087
Let's all try our best.

239
00:12:13,170 --> 00:12:14,129
Let's do this together.

240
00:12:14,213 --> 00:12:16,215
Right. Let's do this together.

241
00:12:19,301 --> 00:12:20,553
Just a little more.

242
00:12:21,178 --> 00:12:22,888
You can be like Hae-kang. Just a bit more.

243
00:12:23,764 --> 00:12:26,100
Almost there. Yes.

244
00:12:26,183 --> 00:12:27,184
Let me ask one thing.

245
00:12:27,268 --> 00:12:29,186
Why are you trying to be a building rep?

246
00:12:29,937 --> 00:12:31,772
I won't stop there.

247
00:12:32,439 --> 00:12:33,274
What?

248
00:12:33,357 --> 00:12:34,400
I'm going to be

249
00:12:35,276 --> 00:12:37,570
the residents' association president.

250
00:12:38,571 --> 00:12:40,656
But why?

251
00:12:41,365 --> 00:12:42,491
I'm a great leader.

252
00:12:44,451 --> 00:12:45,703
A leader?

253
00:12:46,912 --> 00:12:49,582
Don't ignore my sincerity
for making our complex--

254
00:12:49,665 --> 00:12:52,293
Don't say anything.
It'll be something shady anyway.

255
00:12:52,376 --> 00:12:55,921
All I care about is getting my money,
so don't tell me anything.

256
00:12:57,131 --> 00:12:59,174
This won't harm you in any way.

257
00:12:59,925 --> 00:13:02,386
If I become the president,
I'll give you a bonus--

258
00:13:02,469 --> 00:13:03,554
Mr. Park.

259
00:13:03,637 --> 00:13:05,889
Make sure to succeed.

260
00:13:07,766 --> 00:13:10,352
I'm going home now. It's six.

261
00:13:15,899 --> 00:13:16,817
Ms. Kang!

262
00:13:18,277 --> 00:13:19,570
Get home safely.

263
00:13:19,653 --> 00:13:21,447
-Here.
-It's fine.

264
00:13:22,323 --> 00:13:23,365
See you tomorrow.

265
00:13:23,449 --> 00:13:26,201
Get home safe, Ha-ri.

266
00:13:27,828 --> 00:13:30,914
Why did it have to be True Value
of all places?

267
00:13:32,583 --> 00:13:35,127
Ha-jeong will kill me if she finds out.

268
00:13:38,672 --> 00:13:40,299
FRENCH PASTRIES BY LE CORDE D'OR GRADUATE

269
00:13:50,768 --> 00:13:51,977
Kang Ha-jeong.

270
00:13:52,061 --> 00:13:53,437
Go to France.

271
00:13:54,104 --> 00:13:55,856
What? Why would I go there?

272
00:13:55,939 --> 00:13:57,858
When it comes to bread,
it has to be France.

273
00:13:57,941 --> 00:14:00,778
Go and experience the food yourself
and travel a bit.

274
00:14:01,362 --> 00:14:04,031
-Are you crazy? We don't have the money.
-I'm…

275
00:14:05,324 --> 00:14:06,408
a lawyer, remember?

276
00:14:08,160 --> 00:14:11,080
I can't. I have to work.

277
00:14:11,163 --> 00:14:14,416
You're not the only employee there.
You have vacation days left.

278
00:14:14,500 --> 00:14:15,959
Right, but…

279
00:14:16,543 --> 00:14:19,505
There's the building rep
and president election.

280
00:14:21,465 --> 00:14:23,300
This is your only chance, Ha-jeong.

281
00:14:23,967 --> 00:14:25,761
Well, I'll ask.

282
00:14:26,720 --> 00:14:28,347
But I'm not sure they'll let me.

283
00:14:30,015 --> 00:14:31,016
Just talk to them.

284
00:14:34,645 --> 00:14:35,729
Yes?

285
00:14:35,813 --> 00:14:38,315
Mr. Park, are you working
on getting the ten billion?

286
00:14:39,733 --> 00:14:40,693
Three months.

287
00:14:42,027 --> 00:14:43,362
I just need three months.

288
00:14:45,906 --> 00:14:48,367
I know you can do it, Mr. Park.

289
00:14:48,450 --> 00:14:49,994
I believe in you.

290
00:14:50,077 --> 00:14:52,329
Then keep your promise
about returning everything

291
00:14:53,872 --> 00:14:55,040
back to normal.

292
00:14:55,624 --> 00:14:56,834
Just bring the money.

293
00:15:07,428 --> 00:15:08,512
I'm the designated driver.

294
00:15:13,851 --> 00:15:16,270
I'm the designated driver you called for.

295
00:15:16,770 --> 00:15:18,188
This way, sir.

296
00:15:21,108 --> 00:15:23,610
I told you, didn't I?

297
00:15:23,694 --> 00:15:25,654
Park Hae-kang can pull off anything.

298
00:15:26,280 --> 00:15:27,281
Yes. Three months.

299
00:15:28,032 --> 00:15:29,575
He'll get it within three months.

300
00:15:32,619 --> 00:15:33,871
It's nothing.

301
00:15:34,663 --> 00:15:36,874
All I did was make a few calls.

302
00:15:40,210 --> 00:15:41,879
KIM GYEONG-NAM

303
00:15:42,963 --> 00:15:44,631
-Yes?
-Boss.

304
00:15:44,715 --> 00:15:48,343
It seems the Chief really is taking orders
from someone else.

305
00:15:48,927 --> 00:15:50,554
I'll keep tailing him.

306
00:15:50,637 --> 00:15:52,639
Be careful not to get caught.

307
00:15:52,723 --> 00:15:53,557
Yes, sir.

308
00:16:08,238 --> 00:16:09,198
The president is here.

309
00:16:11,075 --> 00:16:11,992
It's the president.

310
00:16:15,079 --> 00:16:17,206
Everyone is here.

311
00:16:17,289 --> 00:16:18,874
I hope everything is going well.

312
00:16:18,957 --> 00:16:20,459
-Yes, sir.
-Yes, sir.

313
00:16:20,542 --> 00:16:21,627
Can you hear me clearly?

314
00:16:21,710 --> 00:16:23,128
-Yes.
-Yes, sir.

315
00:16:23,212 --> 00:16:24,713
Then I'll talk without the mic.

316
00:16:24,797 --> 00:16:27,049
This feels awkward for me.

317
00:16:27,800 --> 00:16:30,803
I've gathered sole candidates
from each district,

318
00:16:30,886 --> 00:16:33,347
including District 1, where I'm running.

319
00:16:33,430 --> 00:16:36,725
Since you're the sole candidates,

320
00:16:36,809 --> 00:16:40,854
you'll be elected
as the representative anyway.

321
00:16:40,938 --> 00:16:42,856
It's quite troubling

322
00:16:42,940 --> 00:16:45,943
how uninterested the residents are
in our complex's affairs.

323
00:16:46,026 --> 00:16:47,402
Everyone's busy making a living.

324
00:16:47,486 --> 00:16:49,196
We should be understanding.

325
00:16:49,279 --> 00:16:53,200
But if we're sole candidates,
do we even need an election?

326
00:16:53,283 --> 00:16:54,993
That's what I mean.

327
00:16:55,077 --> 00:16:57,246
It takes money, time, and resources

328
00:16:57,329 --> 00:16:59,373
-for the election.
-Right.

329
00:17:00,290 --> 00:17:03,877
Well, there are election regulations,
so we have to follow them.

330
00:17:04,461 --> 00:17:07,673
We should uphold basic principles

331
00:17:07,756 --> 00:17:11,301
right here where we live.

332
00:17:11,385 --> 00:17:13,595
That's how basic principles

333
00:17:13,679 --> 00:17:16,890
will be upheld in our society,
and ultimately in Korea.

334
00:17:16,974 --> 00:17:21,478
That's what I've always
thought and believed.

335
00:17:22,062 --> 00:17:23,230
A round of applause.

336
00:17:24,773 --> 00:17:29,403
Our president really has a way with words.

337
00:17:29,486 --> 00:17:31,989
You'll be the president again, won't you?

338
00:17:32,072 --> 00:17:32,990
You should.

339
00:17:34,867 --> 00:17:36,160
Well…

340
00:17:36,243 --> 00:17:38,287
As some of you may know,

341
00:17:38,370 --> 00:17:42,082
I'm not someone
who's attached to positions.

342
00:17:42,166 --> 00:17:43,750
What do you mean?

343
00:17:43,834 --> 00:17:46,545
Who else besides you
would be our association's president?

344
00:17:49,381 --> 00:17:53,927
But I don't see the candidates
from Districts 4 and 6.

345
00:17:54,011 --> 00:17:56,138
The one from District 6 is…

346
00:17:56,221 --> 00:17:57,431
I

347
00:17:58,056 --> 00:17:59,600
didn't invite her.

348
00:18:00,726 --> 00:18:02,311
She's a young mother,

349
00:18:03,520 --> 00:18:05,814
but you know how young mothers are.

350
00:18:06,648 --> 00:18:09,610
They're all talk and no substance.

351
00:18:10,694 --> 00:18:14,948
I just can't stand noisy people.

352
00:18:15,032 --> 00:18:17,159
And as for District 4,

353
00:18:17,242 --> 00:18:19,328
the situation there is a bit different.

354
00:18:23,999 --> 00:18:26,001
-This is fun!
-Stop running, Gyeong-buk.

355
00:18:29,713 --> 00:18:30,756
Gyeong-buk!

356
00:18:30,839 --> 00:18:31,965
I told you not to run.

357
00:18:32,049 --> 00:18:33,926
This isn't Grandma's house.

358
00:18:34,009 --> 00:18:37,596
The downstairs neighbors will complain.
They have students who need to study.

359
00:18:41,516 --> 00:18:43,101
What's with this color?

360
00:18:43,810 --> 00:18:45,771
Pink is the perfect color for a man.

361
00:18:45,854 --> 00:18:48,065
What's your candidate number?
I didn't know it,

362
00:18:48,148 --> 00:18:49,816
so I just got your name printed.

363
00:18:49,900 --> 00:18:51,818
He's the sole candidate.
There's no number.

364
00:18:51,902 --> 00:18:54,947
Boss, the campaign truck
will arrive at 11 a.m.

365
00:18:55,030 --> 00:18:56,740
We've prepared the loudest speakers,

366
00:18:56,823 --> 00:18:59,243
so you just have to show up
and hand out business cards.

367
00:18:59,326 --> 00:19:00,410
Your gloves.

368
00:19:00,494 --> 00:19:03,288
Uncle Hae-kang has to shake hands
with everyone, so there's no need.

369
00:19:03,372 --> 00:19:05,082
I'll give them to the others.

370
00:19:05,165 --> 00:19:08,085
I was a facility manager for years.

371
00:19:08,168 --> 00:19:11,505
I'm telling you
a campaign for building rep is excessive.

372
00:19:11,588 --> 00:19:13,507
Are you running for office or what?

373
00:19:13,590 --> 00:19:15,842
-Who the hell would go this far?
-Gyeong-buk.

374
00:19:17,135 --> 00:19:19,930
If he doesn't win the election,
you're dead.

375
00:19:20,889 --> 00:19:22,391
There's a kid here. Watch your words.

376
00:19:23,392 --> 00:19:24,893
Did the rooftop not scare you enough?

377
00:19:24,977 --> 00:19:26,186
Read the room.

378
00:19:26,979 --> 00:19:30,649
He's the sole candidate.
There's no need for business cards.

379
00:19:31,275 --> 00:19:33,485
He doesn't have to do anything…

380
00:19:33,568 --> 00:19:35,153
Oh, Ms. Kang must be here.

381
00:19:37,239 --> 00:19:39,241
Stop stomping around like that!

382
00:19:42,953 --> 00:19:44,621
Everyone, come out here.

383
00:19:45,706 --> 00:19:47,291
FINAL LIST OF BUILDING REP CANDIDATES

384
00:19:47,374 --> 00:19:48,208
CANDIDATE PROFILE

385
00:19:54,965 --> 00:19:57,884
Was having three candidates
part of your perfect plan?

386
00:19:57,968 --> 00:19:59,136
What do we do, Boss?

387
00:19:59,219 --> 00:20:00,429
There are too many candidates.

388
00:20:00,512 --> 00:20:03,140
And she's that woman we saw yesterday.

389
00:20:03,223 --> 00:20:04,850
She was your rival.

390
00:20:07,769 --> 00:20:09,354
You said no one's interested.

391
00:20:11,064 --> 00:20:13,317
Why are there
so many passionate people here?

392
00:20:13,400 --> 00:20:15,360
There's nothing to gain from this.

393
00:20:28,206 --> 00:20:32,169
"I'll be a diligent worker
for True Value."

394
00:20:33,128 --> 00:20:34,880
What do you think, Mr. Kim?

395
00:20:36,173 --> 00:20:37,007
Pardon?

396
00:20:37,090 --> 00:20:39,176
Do you think Park Hae-kang

397
00:20:39,259 --> 00:20:42,054
can be a diligent worker for True Value?

398
00:20:42,679 --> 00:20:43,638
I'm not sure.

399
00:20:53,231 --> 00:20:57,027
I spent a fortune on the landscaping here.

400
00:21:00,447 --> 00:21:01,823
I said I'd carry it.

401
00:21:01,907 --> 00:21:03,283
You can take it from here.

402
00:21:06,244 --> 00:21:08,372
I told you,

403
00:21:08,455 --> 00:21:11,333
you shouldn't have booked tickets
without even asking me.

404
00:21:11,416 --> 00:21:15,879
I have no choice but to go
since we can't get a refund, but…

405
00:21:15,962 --> 00:21:17,464
Don't worry.

406
00:21:17,547 --> 00:21:18,799
Just go and experience

407
00:21:18,882 --> 00:21:21,009
every kind of bread there is,
starting with baguettes.

408
00:21:21,927 --> 00:21:24,888
I can't believe you did this for me.

409
00:21:26,056 --> 00:21:27,933
You have your passport, don't you? Go.

410
00:21:29,601 --> 00:21:31,311
Thank you, Ha-ri.

411
00:21:31,937 --> 00:21:33,063
I'm sorry.

412
00:21:33,146 --> 00:21:36,400
But what excuse will I use to stop her
from coming to work in two weeks?

413
00:21:37,275 --> 00:21:38,360
I'll really get going now.

414
00:21:38,443 --> 00:21:39,903
-Thank you.
-Go on.

415
00:21:44,825 --> 00:21:45,742
Please…

416
00:21:46,368 --> 00:21:47,953
I won't mind a foreign brother-in-law,

417
00:21:48,036 --> 00:21:50,747
so can't you meet someone there
and just keep living there?

418
00:21:50,831 --> 00:21:52,666
Bye.

419
00:21:52,749 --> 00:21:53,708
Take care!

420
00:22:02,259 --> 00:22:06,054
I'm Candidate 3 for District 4,

421
00:22:06,138 --> 00:22:07,931
Park Hae-kang!

422
00:22:09,558 --> 00:22:10,934
I'll do my best!

423
00:22:11,017 --> 00:22:14,062
I'm your diligent worker,
Candidate 3, Park Hae-kang!

424
00:22:15,021 --> 00:22:16,940
TRUE VALUE'S DILIGENT WORKER
PARK HAE-KANG

425
00:22:17,023 --> 00:22:18,191
Park Hae-kang!

426
00:22:18,775 --> 00:22:22,028
Candidate 3, Park Hae-kang!

427
00:22:23,947 --> 00:22:25,407
Hello!

428
00:22:25,490 --> 00:22:27,075
I'm Candidate 3, Park Hae-kang!

429
00:22:27,159 --> 00:22:29,870
Nice to meet you.
I'm Candidate 3, Park Hae-kang.

430
00:22:31,830 --> 00:22:34,166
Candidate 3.

431
00:22:35,125 --> 00:22:36,459
We're getting so many complaints.

432
00:22:36,543 --> 00:22:38,170
They said they'll call the police.

433
00:22:39,296 --> 00:22:40,130
This is new.

434
00:22:40,213 --> 00:22:41,381
I'll do my best!

435
00:22:42,632 --> 00:22:45,010
District 4, building representative

436
00:22:45,093 --> 00:22:47,304
-Candidate 3, Park Hae-kang!
-True Value, Park Hae-kang!

437
00:22:47,387 --> 00:22:49,264
True Value, Park Hae-kang!

438
00:22:49,347 --> 00:22:50,348
Ms. Kang!

439
00:22:50,432 --> 00:22:52,684
-Candidate 3, Park Hae-kang!
-Ms. Kang!

440
00:22:52,767 --> 00:22:55,353
Ms. Kang! Jump!

441
00:22:55,437 --> 00:22:56,938
-I'll do my best!
-Jump!

442
00:23:02,152 --> 00:23:04,446
We can't campaign anymore.
What do we do now?

443
00:23:05,363 --> 00:23:07,199
Are you going to keep
pacing around like that?

444
00:23:07,741 --> 00:23:12,329
This is the perfect time for him
to finish thinking

445
00:23:12,412 --> 00:23:16,124
and come up with an amazing idea…

446
00:23:22,505 --> 00:23:24,674
Move aside. Let me see.

447
00:23:27,052 --> 00:23:29,763
Candidate 2, Shin Bong-su.
His campaign pledge is…

448
00:23:30,430 --> 00:23:32,515
"I'll create a designated smoking area."

449
00:23:33,391 --> 00:23:36,478
But isn't this a non-smoking
apartment complex?

450
00:23:36,561 --> 00:23:38,396
There are children everywhere.

451
00:23:38,480 --> 00:23:40,982
The mothers won't just let him
make a smoking area.

452
00:23:41,066 --> 00:23:42,317
They won't vote for him. He's out.

453
00:23:43,777 --> 00:23:45,570
Next, Candidate 1. Jang Suk-jin.

454
00:23:45,654 --> 00:23:47,781
"I'll have Exit 3
of Line 10's Oman Station

455
00:23:47,864 --> 00:23:50,033
relocated to the front
of True Value State."

456
00:23:50,116 --> 00:23:53,119
How would she relocate a subway exit?

457
00:23:53,203 --> 00:23:54,746
Is this even feasible?

458
00:23:54,829 --> 00:23:57,540
A proposal to connect the station
to True Value was turned down,

459
00:23:57,624 --> 00:24:00,627
but some residents still haven't
given up hope and are protesting.

460
00:24:00,710 --> 00:24:02,754
-That's what we call--
-The PIMFY phenomenon.

461
00:24:03,964 --> 00:24:05,006
How could she do something

462
00:24:05,090 --> 00:24:07,175
even a National Assembly member can't?

463
00:24:07,259 --> 00:24:08,510
She won't win either.

464
00:24:09,594 --> 00:24:11,846
Next, Candidate 3. Park Hae-kang.

465
00:24:11,930 --> 00:24:14,557
"I'll be a diligent worker
for True Value."

466
00:24:15,517 --> 00:24:17,477
How exactly do you plan on doing that?

467
00:24:25,485 --> 00:24:26,444
We'll get to that--

468
00:24:26,528 --> 00:24:27,904
See?

469
00:24:27,988 --> 00:24:30,323
How will you defeat the others
with such complacency?

470
00:24:30,407 --> 00:24:32,701
With that suit, that tone,
and that messy hair…

471
00:24:32,784 --> 00:24:35,245
Do you even want
to become the building rep?

472
00:24:40,583 --> 00:24:42,669
Put your phone on silent during meetings.

473
00:24:43,295 --> 00:24:44,504
Hello?

474
00:24:46,214 --> 00:24:47,507
What do you mean?

475
00:24:48,258 --> 00:24:49,592
Pick up our packages?

476
00:24:53,221 --> 00:24:56,474
You can't just leave
all the packages here!

477
00:24:56,558 --> 00:24:58,351
You're supposed to deliver them!

478
00:24:58,435 --> 00:25:02,022
We can't even if we want to.
They won't let our trucks enter!

479
00:25:02,105 --> 00:25:05,025
We want our packages delivered
conveniently to our doorstep.

480
00:25:05,108 --> 00:25:07,235
We didn't pay to carry them ourselves.

481
00:25:07,319 --> 00:25:08,778
Don't take it out on us.

482
00:25:08,862 --> 00:25:10,989
Tell that to the people
who won't let us enter.

483
00:25:11,072 --> 00:25:13,366
Then you should carry them
to our houses yourselves!

484
00:25:13,450 --> 00:25:15,118
You took our delivery fees, damn it!

485
00:25:15,201 --> 00:25:16,911
You should finish your job!

486
00:25:16,995 --> 00:25:19,497
What? "Damn it"?

487
00:25:22,208 --> 00:25:23,585
You deliver them yourselves.

488
00:25:24,210 --> 00:25:27,047
-You're always making a huge fuss.
-Sir…

489
00:25:27,130 --> 00:25:29,799
This is a delivery crisis.

490
00:25:31,051 --> 00:25:34,721
The trucks make mothers worried
about their kids' safety,

491
00:25:34,804 --> 00:25:37,140
ruin the landscaping,
and pump out exhaust fumes.

492
00:25:37,223 --> 00:25:40,018
So they want them to use
the underground parking lot,

493
00:25:40,101 --> 00:25:41,895
but on the other hand,

494
00:25:41,978 --> 00:25:44,481
look at the trucks. They're huge.

495
00:25:44,564 --> 00:25:46,608
They can't enter the parking lot.

496
00:25:46,691 --> 00:25:48,526
They'll have to modify the trucks,

497
00:25:48,610 --> 00:25:52,280
but that would cost money.
That's why this is happening.

498
00:25:52,947 --> 00:25:56,576
I do understand both sides.
It's a difficult situation.

499
00:25:56,659 --> 00:25:58,370
Let's go get our packages.

500
00:25:58,453 --> 00:25:59,913
-Yeah.
-Okay.

501
00:26:00,455 --> 00:26:01,289
Father.

502
00:26:11,174 --> 00:26:12,550
Are you all right?

503
00:26:12,634 --> 00:26:14,928
Where do you live?
I'll carry that for you.

504
00:26:15,011 --> 00:26:16,554
I live in Building 107.

505
00:26:16,638 --> 00:26:17,555
All right.

506
00:26:38,284 --> 00:26:39,661
This is your chance.

507
00:26:39,744 --> 00:26:40,787
What chance?

508
00:26:40,870 --> 00:26:43,498
Your chance to be a diligent worker
for True Value.

509
00:26:44,791 --> 00:26:46,584
Look at this mess.

510
00:26:53,049 --> 00:26:54,259
You can't…

511
00:26:59,597 --> 00:27:01,141
I'll take care of this problem!

512
00:27:05,353 --> 00:27:06,938
True Value's diligent worker.

513
00:27:08,481 --> 00:27:10,150
I'm Candidate 3 of District 4,

514
00:27:12,152 --> 00:27:13,403
Park Hae-kang.

515
00:27:19,242 --> 00:27:23,246
WIN-WIN

516
00:27:30,295 --> 00:27:31,629
Hello.

517
00:27:32,881 --> 00:27:34,299
District 4's building representative

518
00:27:34,382 --> 00:27:36,259
Candidate 3,

519
00:27:36,342 --> 00:27:38,386
True Value's diligent worker,
Park Hae-kang.

520
00:27:38,470 --> 00:27:39,888
I've done my best

521
00:27:39,971 --> 00:27:44,893
to find a win-win solution between
True Value and the delivery companies.

522
00:27:48,813 --> 00:27:51,024
To prevent package loss,

523
00:27:51,107 --> 00:27:53,318
deliveries will be sorted by building

524
00:27:53,401 --> 00:27:56,988
and handed over directly
after verifying the recipient.

525
00:27:58,072 --> 00:27:59,032
Here you go.

526
00:27:59,115 --> 00:28:00,283
One more thing.

527
00:28:00,366 --> 00:28:03,453
If you tell our partners
your building and unit number,

528
00:28:03,536 --> 00:28:05,455
we'll deliver them

529
00:28:05,538 --> 00:28:06,915
to your doorstep!

530
00:28:16,841 --> 00:28:17,967
Je-gil!

531
00:28:21,763 --> 00:28:23,348
Delivery!

532
00:28:23,973 --> 00:28:25,475
-Hello. Thank you.
-Here you go.

533
00:28:26,434 --> 00:28:27,477
Wait!

534
00:28:28,061 --> 00:28:28,978
Thank you.

535
00:28:30,146 --> 00:28:31,022
This was delicious.

536
00:28:31,105 --> 00:28:32,815
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

537
00:28:34,567 --> 00:28:36,152
I'm Candidate 3, Park Hae-kang.

538
00:28:36,236 --> 00:28:37,862
-Candidate 3, Park Hae-kang.
-Yes.

539
00:28:38,446 --> 00:28:39,906
Candidate 3, Park Hae-kang!

540
00:28:39,989 --> 00:28:42,075
You wouldn't have been able
to carry this here.

541
00:28:42,158 --> 00:28:43,868
-I'm glad we helped out.
-Thank you.

542
00:28:48,748 --> 00:28:50,208
-Wait!
-Over here.

543
00:28:52,877 --> 00:28:53,920
I made some kimchi pancake.

544
00:28:54,003 --> 00:28:55,463
We've been waiting for you. Try this.

545
00:28:55,547 --> 00:28:56,840
Try this too.

546
00:28:56,923 --> 00:28:57,924
Thank you, ladies.

547
00:28:58,007 --> 00:29:00,760
Vote for Candidate Number 3!

548
00:29:00,844 --> 00:29:02,637
You're the best! Visit us again!

549
00:29:02,720 --> 00:29:04,472
Vote for Candidate Number 3!

550
00:29:04,556 --> 00:29:05,723
Unit 1306!

551
00:29:05,807 --> 00:29:07,433
Next time! I'm busy!

552
00:29:07,517 --> 00:29:08,893
When will you be back?

553
00:29:11,437 --> 00:29:13,189
Delivery!

554
00:29:13,273 --> 00:29:15,650
Candidate 3, Park Hae-kang!

555
00:29:15,733 --> 00:29:17,026
Keep up the good work!

556
00:29:18,111 --> 00:29:19,529
That's a lot of candidates.

557
00:29:19,612 --> 00:29:21,155
Yeah.

558
00:29:21,239 --> 00:29:23,366
But if I were in District 4,

559
00:29:23,449 --> 00:29:25,535
-I'd want to pick Candidate 3.
-Right?

560
00:29:25,618 --> 00:29:27,954
I should tell Min-ji's mom
to vote for him.

561
00:29:28,037 --> 00:29:28,872
You should.

562
00:29:28,955 --> 00:29:30,915
It's not easy delivering packages.

563
00:29:30,999 --> 00:29:33,668
Why'd the residents' association
stop the trucks from entering?

564
00:29:33,751 --> 00:29:35,461
-It's such a pain.
-Right?

565
00:29:35,545 --> 00:29:37,964
Hello.

566
00:29:39,007 --> 00:29:40,592
You're from Building 108, aren't you?

567
00:29:40,675 --> 00:29:41,801
-Yes.
-Yes.

568
00:29:41,885 --> 00:29:44,596
But we all have hands, you know.

569
00:29:44,679 --> 00:29:46,931
Everyone can just
take their own packages home.

570
00:29:47,015 --> 00:29:48,683
How long will they keep this up?

571
00:29:48,766 --> 00:29:51,561
It's not like they'll keep
delivering packages for us forever.

572
00:29:52,270 --> 00:29:55,940
This is what we call vote-buying promises.

573
00:29:56,024 --> 00:29:58,026
You should know that.

574
00:29:58,818 --> 00:30:01,905
Pay attention to the other candidates too.

575
00:30:01,988 --> 00:30:02,864
-Right.
-Sure.

576
00:30:02,947 --> 00:30:04,699
Please show some interest!

577
00:30:04,782 --> 00:30:07,160
Reject Oman Station Exit 3.

578
00:30:09,704 --> 00:30:11,414
-I'm here.
-Welcome.

579
00:30:11,497 --> 00:30:12,790
-Hi.
-Hi.

580
00:30:14,375 --> 00:30:16,169
Wow, this is your breakfast?

581
00:30:16,252 --> 00:30:17,629
You even have grilled hairtail.

582
00:30:17,712 --> 00:30:19,631
You haven't had breakfast,
have you, Ms. Kang?

583
00:30:19,714 --> 00:30:21,341
Sit wherever you'd like.

584
00:30:22,675 --> 00:30:25,803
This seat is comfy.

585
00:30:25,887 --> 00:30:27,555
What is it? What?

586
00:30:27,639 --> 00:30:29,182
Mom, sit next to me.

587
00:30:29,265 --> 00:30:30,183
Over here.

588
00:30:30,892 --> 00:30:31,726
Sure.

589
00:30:35,521 --> 00:30:36,689
Have some.

590
00:30:39,817 --> 00:30:41,694
It's a mountain of rice.

591
00:30:41,778 --> 00:30:43,738
Let me know if that's not enough.

592
00:30:43,821 --> 00:30:45,573
-Not enough?
-Just in case.

593
00:30:50,536 --> 00:30:52,789
-Have some bulgogi.
-It's fine.

594
00:30:52,872 --> 00:30:55,083
It's really tasty. It melts in your mouth.

595
00:30:57,835 --> 00:30:58,920
Unbelievable.

596
00:30:59,587 --> 00:31:01,464
Aren't you eating, Mr. Park?

597
00:31:01,547 --> 00:31:03,925
This is enough for me.

598
00:31:04,509 --> 00:31:05,802
Espresso?

599
00:31:05,885 --> 00:31:07,720
You're no fun at all.

600
00:31:17,563 --> 00:31:18,439
Hey, kid.

601
00:31:19,649 --> 00:31:21,442
What was your name again? Gyeong-nam?

602
00:31:21,526 --> 00:31:23,111
-What?
-What?

603
00:31:23,194 --> 00:31:24,112
That's me.

604
00:31:24,779 --> 00:31:25,822
Right.

605
00:31:25,905 --> 00:31:27,240
Mom.

606
00:31:27,323 --> 00:31:29,325
I'm Gyeong-buk.

607
00:31:29,409 --> 00:31:30,535
Kim Gyeong-buk.

608
00:31:31,661 --> 00:31:33,079
Right. Kim Gyeong-buk.

609
00:31:33,579 --> 00:31:34,664
Look.

610
00:31:43,840 --> 00:31:45,466
Do it like this.

611
00:31:47,719 --> 00:31:48,761
-Okay?
-Yes.

612
00:31:48,845 --> 00:31:50,805
This is how you debone hairtail.

613
00:31:51,305 --> 00:31:52,932
You're the best, Mom.

614
00:31:53,016 --> 00:31:54,684
You're like a hairtail genius.

615
00:31:55,977 --> 00:31:56,853
That's enough.

616
00:31:57,353 --> 00:32:00,064
You shouldn't be moved
by something so trivial.

617
00:32:00,148 --> 00:32:02,608
I'm allergic to failure, you know.

618
00:32:03,735 --> 00:32:06,946
So I can't stand seeing people failing.

619
00:32:41,689 --> 00:32:44,650
Can't you see
I'm focused right now, Mr. Kim?

620
00:32:44,734 --> 00:32:47,361
There's something you need to see, sir.

621
00:32:47,987 --> 00:32:48,946
Breaking news.

622
00:32:49,030 --> 00:32:53,034
The candidate sites for the fourth
new town have just been announced.

623
00:32:53,117 --> 00:32:55,244
Sihyeon District of Gwangmyeong,
Gyeonggi Province,

624
00:32:55,328 --> 00:32:56,788
Yusu District of Seongnam,

625
00:32:56,871 --> 00:33:00,124
and the Hanju area
and Suyeong-dong of Incheon

626
00:33:00,208 --> 00:33:02,376
have been chosen as the candidates.

627
00:33:02,460 --> 00:33:04,462
The selection was based
on the evaluation criteria

628
00:33:04,545 --> 00:33:06,631
of the Ministry of Land,
Infrastructure, and Transport…

629
00:33:06,714 --> 00:33:07,715
Oh dear.

630
00:33:08,424 --> 00:33:09,842
Oman wasn't included.

631
00:33:10,593 --> 00:33:13,346
Apparently, it wasn't even mentioned.

632
00:33:13,846 --> 00:33:15,431
Really?

633
00:33:17,558 --> 00:33:19,310
That's pretty upsetting.

634
00:33:20,645 --> 00:33:22,980
Why don't we go fishing
to lighten our mood?

635
00:33:24,315 --> 00:33:26,025
Right now, sir?

636
00:33:26,109 --> 00:33:30,196
Yes. I really want
to go fishing right now.

637
00:33:30,279 --> 00:33:33,407
But it would be too intimate
and gross for us to go alone.

638
00:33:33,491 --> 00:33:35,368
Let's take the elders with us.

639
00:33:37,078 --> 00:33:38,454
I'll make the preparations.

640
00:33:39,455 --> 00:33:40,414
You do that.

641
00:33:48,172 --> 00:33:50,675
I should prepare some saw-edged perch

642
00:33:50,758 --> 00:33:52,009
for the elders to eat.

643
00:34:28,921 --> 00:34:31,174
MINISTER OF LAND, INFRASTRUCTURE,
AND TRANSPORT, KIM JONG-SIK

644
00:34:31,257 --> 00:34:33,050
The fish just aren't biting today.

645
00:34:34,302 --> 00:34:35,136
Seriously.

646
00:34:35,219 --> 00:34:37,722
NATIONAL ASSEMBLY MEMBER
JANG AN-SU

647
00:34:37,805 --> 00:34:40,433
MAYOR OF OMAN CITY
HAN MUN-HO

648
00:34:41,100 --> 00:34:43,394
Let's head back now, Mr. Lee.

649
00:34:43,477 --> 00:34:45,646
But we've spent so much time here.

650
00:34:46,230 --> 00:34:47,899
We can't head back empty-handed.

651
00:34:49,859 --> 00:34:52,361
I am getting kind of hungry, though.

652
00:34:54,572 --> 00:34:55,406
Hey.

653
00:34:56,032 --> 00:34:58,117
-Bring that here.
-Right. Bring it here!

654
00:35:02,496 --> 00:35:03,331
Ta-da.

655
00:35:03,414 --> 00:35:05,458
I thought something like this
might happen,

656
00:35:05,541 --> 00:35:09,712
so I got some wild-caught saw-edged perch
from Jeju Island myself.

657
00:35:10,963 --> 00:35:12,548
You're so prepared.

658
00:35:13,132 --> 00:35:14,800
Mayor, here you go.

659
00:35:15,968 --> 00:35:17,011
Open up.

660
00:35:18,512 --> 00:35:20,348
This is embarrassing.

661
00:35:20,431 --> 00:35:22,308
Sir, please. Just once.

662
00:35:22,391 --> 00:35:23,601
Open up.

663
00:35:24,769 --> 00:35:26,020
All right.

664
00:35:27,605 --> 00:35:30,399
That's right. Very good.

665
00:35:32,610 --> 00:35:33,527
Wait, what…

666
00:35:35,112 --> 00:35:37,531
Open his mouth wider.

667
00:35:39,617 --> 00:35:41,452
Sir, let me give you some
red pepper paste.

668
00:35:47,124 --> 00:35:48,709
Mr. Lee!

669
00:35:48,793 --> 00:35:51,170
What the hell are you doing?

670
00:35:51,254 --> 00:35:52,129
Have you lost it?

671
00:35:52,838 --> 00:35:55,675
You can't even do your job,
you can't catch any fish,

672
00:35:56,467 --> 00:35:58,386
but you still want some saw-edged perch.

673
00:35:58,469 --> 00:36:01,180
Don't you think that would irritate me?

674
00:36:01,847 --> 00:36:04,100
You really are clueless.

675
00:36:04,850 --> 00:36:07,144
You took my money

676
00:36:07,228 --> 00:36:08,938
but blew the new town deal.

677
00:36:09,021 --> 00:36:11,357
Did you really think I'd rent a boat

678
00:36:11,440 --> 00:36:14,443
and prepare all this for you
out of gratitude?

679
00:36:15,069 --> 00:36:16,529
Mr. Lee,

680
00:36:16,612 --> 00:36:19,615
sometimes,
we need to let go of the small things

681
00:36:19,699 --> 00:36:20,992
for the bigger picture…

682
00:36:24,078 --> 00:36:25,288
What bigger picture?

683
00:36:26,789 --> 00:36:29,500
Do you know what Won Bin
said in that movie?

684
00:36:33,254 --> 00:36:35,423
"You only live for tomorrow, don't you?"

685
00:36:36,507 --> 00:36:38,467
"I only live for today."

686
00:36:39,051 --> 00:36:42,346
"And you won't survive
against a guy who lives only for today."

687
00:36:48,019 --> 00:36:51,564
I'm someone who only lives for today,
so if anyone pisses me off,

688
00:36:52,273 --> 00:36:55,067
I have to take it out on them right away.

689
00:36:55,151 --> 00:36:56,110
Minister.

690
00:36:57,028 --> 00:36:58,821
Why don't you take a dip?

691
00:37:06,120 --> 00:37:08,497
Let's talk this out!

692
00:37:08,581 --> 00:37:12,752
I'll do my best to get
the new town project approved!

693
00:37:12,835 --> 00:37:14,211
I swear!

694
00:37:16,505 --> 00:37:17,965
I can't swim!

695
00:37:19,467 --> 00:37:23,179
Mr. Lee! Help me!

696
00:37:24,221 --> 00:37:26,724
I'll return everything you gave me.

697
00:37:26,807 --> 00:37:31,103
I'm sorry, but Oman was ruled out
due to the regulations.

698
00:37:31,187 --> 00:37:34,440
That was because
you didn't do your job properly.

699
00:37:34,523 --> 00:37:36,776
If I gave you bullets
to get them on our side, then…

700
00:37:36,859 --> 00:37:38,235
Bang, bang!

701
00:37:39,737 --> 00:37:41,364
You should've shot them.

702
00:37:42,198 --> 00:37:43,991
But you just took them all for yourself.

703
00:37:45,284 --> 00:37:46,702
How did you think this would play out?

704
00:37:48,120 --> 00:37:51,499
You need a good scolding today.

705
00:37:54,335 --> 00:37:55,461
What are you doing?

706
00:37:55,544 --> 00:37:57,004
Mr. Lee!

707
00:38:00,591 --> 00:38:01,467
We'll…

708
00:38:02,134 --> 00:38:04,553
We'll take care of this.

709
00:38:04,637 --> 00:38:05,888
Will you?

710
00:38:05,971 --> 00:38:07,139
Of course.

711
00:38:07,765 --> 00:38:09,517
Can I trust you?

712
00:38:09,600 --> 00:38:10,559
-Yes.
-Of course.

713
00:38:10,643 --> 00:38:12,520
If you disappoint me again,

714
00:38:13,396 --> 00:38:15,189
I'll really lose my head.

715
00:38:28,577 --> 00:38:30,621
This really melts in your mouth.

716
00:38:34,333 --> 00:38:35,209
Hey.

717
00:38:36,585 --> 00:38:38,045
I'm from Unit 1802.

718
00:38:38,129 --> 00:38:42,174
If there's anything broken or ruined,
you're dead.

719
00:38:43,801 --> 00:38:44,844
Be careful with it.

720
00:38:45,636 --> 00:38:47,138
-Yes, sir.
-Okay.

721
00:38:48,681 --> 00:38:49,682
Hey!

722
00:38:50,808 --> 00:38:53,602
Don't take the elevator.
Carry them up the stairs.

723
00:38:53,686 --> 00:38:56,772
I hate it when delivery guys
hold up the elevator.

724
00:38:58,399 --> 00:39:00,484
What? You got a problem?

725
00:39:03,612 --> 00:39:04,947
What's with the face?

726
00:39:07,158 --> 00:39:10,035
Did something happen when you were born,
or is it your genes?

727
00:39:10,119 --> 00:39:11,162
That jerk.

728
00:39:11,245 --> 00:39:12,371
Did he just hit him?

729
00:39:14,206 --> 00:39:16,375
He's a voter in District 4.

730
00:39:16,459 --> 00:39:18,127
-Boss.
-Boss.

731
00:39:18,210 --> 00:39:20,504
-How could you…
-You rude jerks.

732
00:39:37,855 --> 00:39:39,106
I'm aching all over.

733
00:39:39,648 --> 00:39:41,901
I didn't even do much.
Why am I so exhausted?

734
00:39:42,610 --> 00:39:43,444
Mr. Park.

735
00:39:43,527 --> 00:39:45,613
Can I have a pain relief patch too?

736
00:39:46,614 --> 00:39:47,448
Here.

737
00:39:49,450 --> 00:39:50,743
Thanks.

738
00:39:52,995 --> 00:39:55,372
I feel like I lost five kilos already.

739
00:39:55,956 --> 00:39:58,626
Can you order us some chicken?

740
00:39:58,709 --> 00:39:59,752
My legs…

741
00:40:02,922 --> 00:40:07,092
Boss, the apartment complex forum
is buzzing about this.

742
00:40:07,176 --> 00:40:08,135
Really?

743
00:40:08,761 --> 00:40:10,054
Let me see. Bring it here.

744
00:40:19,355 --> 00:40:20,397
They're all grateful

745
00:40:20,481 --> 00:40:22,525
and say that it was really helpful.

746
00:40:22,608 --> 00:40:25,819
They're calling you the hero
who solved the delivery crisis.

747
00:40:29,698 --> 00:40:30,908
Hang on.

748
00:40:30,991 --> 00:40:32,743
Scroll back up a bit.

749
00:40:33,953 --> 00:40:36,413
"Request to discontinue…"

750
00:40:37,373 --> 00:40:38,374
Give me that.

751
00:40:39,583 --> 00:40:41,001
"Discontinue the delivery service?"

752
00:40:41,085 --> 00:40:42,044
Why?

753
00:40:42,836 --> 00:40:43,879
What happened here?

754
00:40:45,631 --> 00:40:48,175
"All my deliveries are damaged,

755
00:40:48,259 --> 00:40:50,135
and things have gone missing."

756
00:40:50,219 --> 00:40:52,429
"Shouldn't we verify
the delivery workers' identities?"

757
00:40:53,264 --> 00:40:55,558
They were getting paid.
They wouldn't have done this.

758
00:41:01,230 --> 00:41:03,649
Take a good look at this.

759
00:41:07,528 --> 00:41:08,946
Tell me honestly.

760
00:41:12,866 --> 00:41:14,660
Who messed with the deliveries?

761
00:41:15,286 --> 00:41:18,622
Boss, you can chop our hands off
if we really did this.

762
00:41:18,706 --> 00:41:20,499
We're not in some gang, you know.

763
00:41:20,583 --> 00:41:23,544
I'm not chopping your hands off.
I'm docking your pay.

764
00:41:23,627 --> 00:41:25,296
-It's not us!
-We really didn't do it!

765
00:41:25,379 --> 00:41:27,631
We don't even know what's in the parcels.

766
00:41:27,715 --> 00:41:29,633
How would we mess with them?

767
00:41:29,717 --> 00:41:32,094
Then what's this anonymous post?

768
00:41:32,177 --> 00:41:34,305
The kimchi was leaking,
some apples were missing,

769
00:41:34,388 --> 00:41:37,224
and the potatoes and sweet potatoes
were all damaged.

770
00:41:37,308 --> 00:41:40,811
Boss, by any chance,
is it Unit 902 in Building 112?

771
00:41:40,894 --> 00:41:42,646
They always order heavy stuff,

772
00:41:42,730 --> 00:41:44,857
so I remember the address.

773
00:41:44,940 --> 00:41:46,275
I think it is.

774
00:41:48,652 --> 00:41:50,696
The proof of delivery photos look fine.

775
00:41:54,033 --> 00:41:56,368
Boss. Unit 902 of Building 112

776
00:41:56,452 --> 00:41:59,371
is Candidate Jang's place.

777
00:42:08,213 --> 00:42:11,425
She's going negative
over a building rep election?

778
00:42:12,134 --> 00:42:13,677
Negative…

779
00:42:13,761 --> 00:42:14,845
What does that mean?

780
00:42:17,389 --> 00:42:19,350
-It's English.
-It's just a term.

781
00:42:20,351 --> 00:42:23,479
It's "negative campaigning"
when you make baseless accusations

782
00:42:23,562 --> 00:42:25,856
about your opponent during an election.

783
00:42:25,939 --> 00:42:29,068
This is all because
she's feeling threatened

784
00:42:29,151 --> 00:42:30,736
by Mr. Park pulling ahead.

785
00:42:31,528 --> 00:42:33,864
Still, how can she lie like this?

786
00:42:33,947 --> 00:42:35,866
Elections are always messy.

787
00:42:35,949 --> 00:42:37,868
That's democracy for you.

788
00:42:37,951 --> 00:42:39,203
What should we do?

789
00:42:39,286 --> 00:42:41,580
It's obvious, isn't it?

790
00:42:41,664 --> 00:42:43,123
Fight negative with negative.

791
00:42:43,207 --> 00:42:45,042
Negative with negative…

792
00:42:46,460 --> 00:42:48,170
Let's take down

793
00:42:48,253 --> 00:42:49,630
-Jang Suk-jin.
-Yes.

794
00:42:49,713 --> 00:42:50,714
What?

795
00:42:50,798 --> 00:42:53,133
We don't need to do the same to her…

796
00:42:53,217 --> 00:42:54,843
Do you guys remember

797
00:42:55,552 --> 00:42:58,681
the day we caught the Salamander

798
00:42:58,764 --> 00:43:00,599
from Incheon's Sewer Gang?

799
00:43:42,433 --> 00:43:43,809
I missed you, Salamander.

800
00:44:12,963 --> 00:44:14,089
Watch out.

801
00:44:14,631 --> 00:44:16,049
Park Hae-kang.

802
00:44:16,842 --> 00:44:19,052
Do you think you've won?

803
00:44:23,724 --> 00:44:25,058
What are you waiting for?

804
00:44:35,319 --> 00:44:37,780
Boss, what's going on?

805
00:44:38,405 --> 00:44:39,406
Park Hae-kang.

806
00:44:39,490 --> 00:44:42,743
You've really underestimated me.

807
00:44:42,826 --> 00:44:45,245
What are you waiting for? Crush them!

808
00:44:53,045 --> 00:44:54,588
We almost died back then.

809
00:44:54,671 --> 00:44:56,423
What do you think was the reason?

810
00:44:56,507 --> 00:44:57,633
We were too complacent.

811
00:44:58,884 --> 00:45:00,552
That was our problem.

812
00:45:00,636 --> 00:45:02,554
If we're complacent about this too,

813
00:45:02,638 --> 00:45:04,765
Jang Suk-jin could become
like the Salamander.

814
00:45:04,848 --> 00:45:06,558
We have to crush her before then.

815
00:45:06,642 --> 00:45:09,811
I'll crush Jang Suk-jin myself.

816
00:45:11,813 --> 00:45:14,650
You can't even stand up.
What could you possibly do?

817
00:45:15,150 --> 00:45:16,485
Let him go and get some exercise.

818
00:45:16,568 --> 00:45:17,569
Hey!

819
00:45:18,195 --> 00:45:19,404
What is it?

820
00:45:21,031 --> 00:45:21,949
Academic fraud.

821
00:45:22,032 --> 00:45:25,744
Nothing is more serious
than academic fraud in Korea.

822
00:45:26,620 --> 00:45:27,621
Let's go with this.

823
00:45:28,997 --> 00:45:30,832
Academic fraud…

824
00:45:35,337 --> 00:45:36,672
REPORTING JANG SUK-JIN'S ACADEMIC FRAUD

825
00:45:37,381 --> 00:45:40,467
But what if she really did graduate
from Ilhwa Women's University?

826
00:45:40,551 --> 00:45:42,719
I told you about negative campaigns.

827
00:45:42,803 --> 00:45:44,930
It doesn't matter
whether it's true or not.

828
00:45:45,013 --> 00:45:48,058
The point is to make it into a scandal.

829
00:45:48,809 --> 00:45:49,726
Right.

830
00:45:54,940 --> 00:45:56,275
REPORTING JANG SUK-JIN'S ACADEMIC FRAUD

831
00:45:56,358 --> 00:45:58,026
What? Is this true?

832
00:45:58,110 --> 00:45:59,570
She's unbelievable.

833
00:45:59,653 --> 00:46:01,405
Shouldn't she withdraw her candidacy?

834
00:46:01,488 --> 00:46:02,489
Academic fraud over this?

835
00:46:02,573 --> 00:46:03,991
What is she even doing at her age?

836
00:46:04,074 --> 00:46:06,159
We can't have someone like her
as our building rep.

837
00:46:08,328 --> 00:46:10,497
Write at least ten comments
under different usernames.

838
00:46:10,581 --> 00:46:11,540
-Okay.
-Yes, Boss.

839
00:46:12,207 --> 00:46:13,041
And the Lizard?

840
00:46:21,800 --> 00:46:24,052
How can you not know?

841
00:46:24,136 --> 00:46:27,598
You're the management office.
That doesn't make sense.

842
00:46:27,681 --> 00:46:31,226
Ma'am, it's an anonymous board
for a reason.

843
00:46:31,310 --> 00:46:32,728
We can't know who wrote it either.

844
00:46:32,811 --> 00:46:34,855
Hey. I promise,

845
00:46:34,938 --> 00:46:38,609
I won't tell anyone I heard it
from the management office.

846
00:46:38,692 --> 00:46:42,112
So you can just tell me.

847
00:46:42,195 --> 00:46:43,447
Ma'am.

848
00:46:43,530 --> 00:46:45,741
No matter how much you pester us,

849
00:46:45,824 --> 00:46:47,117
we really have no idea.

850
00:46:47,743 --> 00:46:49,328
What do you mean?

851
00:46:49,411 --> 00:46:50,412
You have stuff like

852
00:46:50,495 --> 00:46:52,372
IP tracking or whatever.

853
00:46:52,456 --> 00:46:54,291
You can find them if you do that!

854
00:46:55,000 --> 00:46:58,003
We're not the police.
We can't do stuff like that.

855
00:46:58,587 --> 00:47:01,173
Fine. Then call the cops.

856
00:47:01,256 --> 00:47:02,883
Report this to the cops!

857
00:47:02,966 --> 00:47:06,386
Call the National Forensic Service too.
I can't stand this.

858
00:47:06,470 --> 00:47:08,388
This is so unfair!

859
00:47:08,472 --> 00:47:09,806
Come on…

860
00:47:09,890 --> 00:47:11,350
Why are they doing this to me?

861
00:47:11,433 --> 00:47:12,476
Ma'am.

862
00:47:12,559 --> 00:47:14,519
Mr. Choi, I'm innocent.

863
00:47:14,603 --> 00:47:17,105
I really did graduate
from Ilhwa Women's University.

864
00:47:17,189 --> 00:47:19,566
Ma'am, just calm down first.

865
00:47:19,650 --> 00:47:21,276
If you explain to everyone

866
00:47:21,360 --> 00:47:23,904
that you really did graduate
from Ilhwa Women's University,

867
00:47:23,987 --> 00:47:25,739
-they'll understand.
-Mr. Choi.

868
00:47:26,448 --> 00:47:28,700
-I know.
-Know what?

869
00:47:28,784 --> 00:47:30,202
I know who did this.

870
00:47:31,286 --> 00:47:34,331
I just don't have clear evidence,
but I have a hunch.

871
00:47:34,414 --> 00:47:37,209
-I know who did it.
-Who is it?

872
00:47:38,085 --> 00:47:40,629
It's Candidate 3, Park Hae-kang.

873
00:47:43,340 --> 00:47:46,051
He's trying to defeat me in the election.

874
00:47:46,134 --> 00:47:48,553
This is all his doing! It was his scheme!

875
00:47:48,637 --> 00:47:49,930
ACADEMIC AWARD, SCHOLARSHIP AWARD

876
00:47:56,728 --> 00:47:59,022
Ma'am, I didn't just graduate.

877
00:47:59,106 --> 00:48:01,316
I was at the top of my class.

878
00:48:01,400 --> 00:48:02,484
-You hear?
-All right.

879
00:48:02,567 --> 00:48:04,027
I'll call you!

880
00:48:04,111 --> 00:48:07,781
-Hello.
-Please read this. I'm a victim.

881
00:48:07,864 --> 00:48:09,491
They spread lies about me.

882
00:48:09,574 --> 00:48:11,410
-I'm so upset.
-Right.

883
00:48:11,493 --> 00:48:13,036
Please just read this.

884
00:48:13,120 --> 00:48:14,079
Come on!

885
00:48:14,162 --> 00:48:16,456
Why would you throw it away?

886
00:48:21,253 --> 00:48:23,171
Why did he throw it away?

887
00:48:26,883 --> 00:48:28,260
I said I can go alone.

888
00:48:28,802 --> 00:48:31,471
Won't people think it's strange
if they see a mother

889
00:48:31,555 --> 00:48:33,265
heading out alone late at night?

890
00:48:33,765 --> 00:48:36,059
Just act like we're taking a walk together

891
00:48:36,143 --> 00:48:39,354
and slip out quietly
through the back gate.

892
00:48:39,438 --> 00:48:40,939
Why are you so meticulous?

893
00:48:42,774 --> 00:48:43,817
We'll look like strangers.

894
00:48:43,900 --> 00:48:45,861
Just hold onto my arm.

895
00:48:46,945 --> 00:48:50,031
Married couples don't normally
walk like that, you know.

896
00:48:50,115 --> 00:48:52,200
It's more natural to walk apart
like strangers.

897
00:48:52,993 --> 00:48:53,869
Ms. Kang.

898
00:48:55,370 --> 00:48:58,331
Don't you remember the clause
in our contract

899
00:48:58,832 --> 00:48:59,791
about active cooperation?

900
00:49:01,543 --> 00:49:04,296
Don't you see how cooperative I am
even while walking?

901
00:49:08,049 --> 00:49:09,176
Just hold my arm.

902
00:49:24,024 --> 00:49:24,900
Peek-a-boo!

903
00:49:30,280 --> 00:49:33,158
After all that education I gave you,

904
00:49:33,241 --> 00:49:34,785
you still don't salute me?

905
00:49:37,579 --> 00:49:39,748
Are your knees broken?
You're still sitting?

906
00:49:39,831 --> 00:49:42,334
How rude, greeting me sitting down.

907
00:49:42,417 --> 00:49:44,419
Let me give you a proper education today.

908
00:49:47,422 --> 00:49:48,507
Wait.

909
00:49:49,174 --> 00:49:50,300
What's he doing?

910
00:49:51,718 --> 00:49:52,928
Just go home, Ms. Kang.

911
00:49:53,011 --> 00:49:54,679
I will.

912
00:49:54,763 --> 00:49:55,889
But first…

913
00:49:57,015 --> 00:49:58,225
That asshole!

914
00:49:59,017 --> 00:50:00,435
Let go of me!

915
00:50:00,519 --> 00:50:02,229
That asshole is a voter too.

916
00:50:02,854 --> 00:50:04,648
It won't look good for a candidate's wife

917
00:50:04,731 --> 00:50:06,733
to fight with a voter.

918
00:50:08,610 --> 00:50:11,488
A voter? Seriously?
Is building rep that important?

919
00:50:12,072 --> 00:50:13,365
Mr. Park.

920
00:50:13,448 --> 00:50:15,826
You might become
the building representative this way,

921
00:50:15,909 --> 00:50:18,161
but you're hopeless as a human being.

922
00:50:24,167 --> 00:50:25,502
Mr. Park, wait.

923
00:50:25,585 --> 00:50:26,962
Hang on!

924
00:50:27,045 --> 00:50:29,297
Go home if you want
the rest of your money.

925
00:50:29,381 --> 00:50:30,632
Didn't you see him getting hit?

926
00:50:30,715 --> 00:50:32,467
I'm choosing not to see it.

927
00:50:32,551 --> 00:50:33,426
Go.

928
00:50:35,262 --> 00:50:36,179
Mr. Park!

929
00:50:42,602 --> 00:50:44,145
He's the asshole.

930
00:50:47,816 --> 00:50:49,234
Do you even know who I am?

931
00:50:49,317 --> 00:50:53,071
I was the boss of the Oasis Gang,
you idiot!

932
00:50:53,154 --> 00:50:54,489
Why won't you salute me?

933
00:50:54,573 --> 00:50:55,949
You're dead!

934
00:50:57,617 --> 00:50:59,578
You're dead today.

935
00:51:00,745 --> 00:51:01,913
Stop!

936
00:51:02,998 --> 00:51:04,082
And who are you?

937
00:51:04,165 --> 00:51:06,877
Get lost. I'm going to take care
of this idiot and go home.

938
00:51:06,960 --> 00:51:08,169
Me too.

939
00:51:08,253 --> 00:51:09,921
I'd like to hurry home too.

940
00:51:10,547 --> 00:51:12,799
But someone told me
I was hopeless as a human being,

941
00:51:12,883 --> 00:51:14,134
and I can't shake it off.

942
00:51:14,217 --> 00:51:16,636
What are you saying?
Is this a monologue or what?

943
00:51:16,720 --> 00:51:18,221
Do you know who I am?

944
00:51:18,305 --> 00:51:20,098
You said you were the boss
of the Oasis Gang.

945
00:51:20,181 --> 00:51:22,225
Right. Do you have a death wish?

946
00:51:22,309 --> 00:51:24,102
You've never seen his face before,
have you?

947
00:51:24,853 --> 00:51:25,687
Would you like to?

948
00:51:28,815 --> 00:51:31,860
Look at my face properly
so you won't forget.

949
00:51:34,237 --> 00:51:36,239
Who would want to watch you
eating ramyeon?

950
00:51:36,323 --> 00:51:37,532
This won't do.

951
00:51:37,616 --> 00:51:39,326
-Really?
-You need to eat way more.

952
00:51:39,409 --> 00:51:40,452
You're right…

953
00:51:41,745 --> 00:51:43,496
Hey, look. They're fighting.

954
00:51:43,580 --> 00:51:45,749
-Awesome!
-Film it.

955
00:51:45,832 --> 00:51:47,792
Look!

956
00:51:47,876 --> 00:51:49,127
He's dead.

957
00:51:51,004 --> 00:51:52,005
Where are you going?

958
00:51:53,757 --> 00:51:54,674
Stay back!

959
00:51:54,758 --> 00:51:55,800
Stay back!

960
00:51:55,884 --> 00:51:57,344
Where are you going? We're not done yet.

961
00:51:57,928 --> 00:51:58,929
You should apologize to him.

962
00:51:59,930 --> 00:52:01,056
You're dead.

963
00:52:01,681 --> 00:52:03,767
Come on. Come at me!

964
00:52:11,441 --> 00:52:12,484
No way.

965
00:52:13,485 --> 00:52:15,195
I guess he's kind of cool.

966
00:52:24,371 --> 00:52:26,539
What? Are you insane?

967
00:52:28,375 --> 00:52:29,376
I need to go home.

968
00:52:37,342 --> 00:52:39,636
The building rep election is tomorrow.

969
00:52:39,719 --> 00:52:42,597
Let's do our best for one more day.

970
00:52:43,807 --> 00:52:44,933
One, two, three.

971
00:52:45,016 --> 00:52:46,351
-Win-win!
-Move.

972
00:52:46,434 --> 00:52:47,560
Let's go.

973
00:52:47,644 --> 00:52:49,062
-Let's do this!
-Let's do it!

974
00:52:49,145 --> 00:52:51,356
Let's do it. Don't forget to smile.

975
00:52:51,439 --> 00:52:52,691
"Win-win"? Forget it.

976
00:52:52,774 --> 00:52:54,818
I'll take care of my own packages.

977
00:52:55,485 --> 00:52:56,861
Which building, ma'am?

978
00:52:56,945 --> 00:52:58,530
-Why are you asking me that?
-Hello.

979
00:52:58,613 --> 00:53:01,116
Thank you for everything so far.

980
00:53:01,199 --> 00:53:04,327
But don't ever deliver packages
to our house again.

981
00:53:05,245 --> 00:53:07,706
We're too scared to accept any deliveries.

982
00:53:10,834 --> 00:53:12,669
Where's my package?

983
00:53:15,755 --> 00:53:16,631
Where is it?

984
00:53:20,176 --> 00:53:21,011
What's going on?

985
00:53:21,803 --> 00:53:23,179
What's happening?

986
00:53:23,263 --> 00:53:25,432
Boss, you should take a look at this.

987
00:53:26,016 --> 00:53:28,977
Someone uploaded this YouTube video
on the anonymous board.

988
00:53:29,060 --> 00:53:31,021
DOUBLE LIFE OF THE DELIVERY HERO

989
00:53:32,355 --> 00:53:34,107
It says, "Double life
of the delivery hero."

990
00:53:34,190 --> 00:53:35,984
The comments are going crazy.

991
00:53:36,735 --> 00:53:39,029
"Shouldn't he withdraw his candidacy?"

992
00:53:39,112 --> 00:53:40,697
"What a double life."

993
00:53:42,198 --> 00:53:43,033
Boss.

994
00:53:43,825 --> 00:53:46,202
What on earth happened last night?

995
00:54:02,677 --> 00:54:04,012
The thing is,

996
00:54:04,095 --> 00:54:05,972
Mr. Park wasn't just beating him up.

997
00:54:06,056 --> 00:54:08,725
The guy was hitting the guard,
and Mr. Park saved him.

998
00:54:08,808 --> 00:54:11,853
But that video just showed
the part where he kicked him.

999
00:54:11,936 --> 00:54:14,147
Mr. Park, say something.

1000
00:54:14,230 --> 00:54:15,607
This is all…

1001
00:54:17,525 --> 00:54:18,860
your fault, Ms. Kang.

1002
00:54:20,487 --> 00:54:21,362
What?

1003
00:54:22,405 --> 00:54:23,448
Mr. Park.

1004
00:54:23,531 --> 00:54:26,868
You might become
the building representative this way,

1005
00:54:26,951 --> 00:54:28,661
but you're hopeless as a human being.

1006
00:54:30,080 --> 00:54:31,915
Why would you blame me for that?

1007
00:54:33,333 --> 00:54:36,211
Then what do we do now?

1008
00:54:36,294 --> 00:54:37,295
Are we screwed?

1009
00:54:38,379 --> 00:54:40,340
At this point,

1010
00:54:40,423 --> 00:54:43,760
we've basically lost
the building rep election.

1011
00:54:54,604 --> 00:54:56,856
Yes, this is Park…

1012
00:54:58,650 --> 00:54:59,651
What?

1013
00:55:01,194 --> 00:55:02,278
Okay.

1014
00:55:03,363 --> 00:55:04,239
Where are you going?

1015
00:55:05,532 --> 00:55:07,617
Where is he off to in such a hurry?

1016
00:55:07,700 --> 00:55:09,828
MYUNGJIN UNIVERSITY HOSPITAL

1017
00:55:14,749 --> 00:55:15,792
What's your business, sir?

1018
00:55:15,875 --> 00:55:18,670
I'm Park Hae-kang,
Park Yong-man's guardian.

1019
00:55:27,762 --> 00:55:31,141
You didn't even knock. Mind your manners.

1020
00:55:33,560 --> 00:55:36,604
I said I didn't need my guardian.
Why did you come?

1021
00:55:37,981 --> 00:55:40,650
You didn't take your meds again?
Do you really want to die?

1022
00:55:40,733 --> 00:55:42,861
You really must have a death wish.

1023
00:55:48,575 --> 00:55:51,119
I was so startled.
I thought something happened to you.

1024
00:55:51,202 --> 00:55:53,079
Did you forget my nickname?

1025
00:55:53,163 --> 00:55:55,373
I'm the Phoenix.

1026
00:55:56,040 --> 00:55:58,209
Don't worry. I won't die.

1027
00:56:01,713 --> 00:56:03,756
You'd better keep

1028
00:56:04,382 --> 00:56:05,633
that promise.

1029
00:56:05,717 --> 00:56:07,510
Go away. Gross.

1030
00:56:07,594 --> 00:56:09,095
Let me see.

1031
00:56:09,179 --> 00:56:11,139
Let go of me. That hurts.

1032
00:56:11,222 --> 00:56:12,307
Let me see your face.

1033
00:56:12,390 --> 00:56:14,684
Don't be so touchy-feely.

1034
00:56:19,314 --> 00:56:20,231
How handsome.

1035
00:56:21,441 --> 00:56:23,276
You little brat.

1036
00:56:23,359 --> 00:56:25,570
If I weren't tied up,

1037
00:56:25,653 --> 00:56:28,406
I'd take you down…

1038
00:56:56,392 --> 00:56:57,435
You know,

1039
00:56:58,019 --> 00:57:00,521
I never thought this project would end

1040
00:57:00,605 --> 00:57:02,482
with a single kick from the boss.

1041
00:57:05,735 --> 00:57:08,238
Couldn't he have tolerated some injustice?

1042
00:57:09,155 --> 00:57:10,114
Yeah.

1043
00:57:10,740 --> 00:57:12,659
He should tolerate injustice,

1044
00:57:12,742 --> 00:57:14,869
but not accept losses.

1045
00:57:14,953 --> 00:57:16,204
He's a businessman.

1046
00:57:16,788 --> 00:57:18,581
Today's the election.

1047
00:57:18,665 --> 00:57:20,333
Isn't he going to go vote?

1048
00:57:21,167 --> 00:57:24,128
Wouldn't it be embarrassing
if he ends up with just his own vote?

1049
00:57:25,672 --> 00:57:28,299
Well, I guess you're right.

1050
00:57:28,883 --> 00:57:30,093
Then what do we do now?

1051
00:57:31,261 --> 00:57:34,472
I'm sure he has a plan.

1052
00:57:34,556 --> 00:57:36,474
Right. He should be waking up soon.

1053
00:57:36,558 --> 00:57:37,976
Big Guy, go and prepare breakfast.

1054
00:57:38,518 --> 00:57:40,562
I'm not in the mood to cook.

1055
00:57:40,645 --> 00:57:41,980
Let's just order something.

1056
00:57:42,689 --> 00:57:45,108
Do you really think
he'd have an appetite right now?

1057
00:57:45,191 --> 00:57:47,068
He blew his chance in the election.

1058
00:57:56,661 --> 00:57:57,870
Mr. Park.

1059
00:57:59,831 --> 00:58:01,916
If you're upset
and sulking in your room all day,

1060
00:58:02,000 --> 00:58:03,710
that's your problem.

1061
00:58:03,793 --> 00:58:05,753
It's six now, so I'm heading home.

1062
00:58:05,837 --> 00:58:07,380
Seriously?

1063
00:58:08,923 --> 00:58:10,216
Well,

1064
00:58:10,300 --> 00:58:12,302
I do feel upset too.

1065
00:58:12,385 --> 00:58:13,678
But we have no choice.

1066
00:58:13,761 --> 00:58:15,430
You already lost your chance at winning,

1067
00:58:15,513 --> 00:58:18,099
so there's no need for me
to keep coming here.

1068
00:58:18,182 --> 00:58:20,268
As you know,
you're the one who caused this,

1069
00:58:20,351 --> 00:58:22,645
-so I can't return--
-This is the management office.

1070
00:58:22,729 --> 00:58:26,107
We will now announce
the elected building representatives.

1071
00:58:26,649 --> 00:58:30,361
District 1, Candidate 1, Seo Gang-won.

1072
00:58:30,445 --> 00:58:34,282
District 2, Candidate 1, Kim O-rye.

1073
00:58:34,365 --> 00:58:37,994
District 3, Candidate 1, Lee Seok-man.

1074
00:58:38,077 --> 00:58:41,748
District 4, Candidate 3, Park Hae-kang.

1075
00:58:41,831 --> 00:58:45,793
Uncle got elected!

1076
00:58:48,254 --> 00:58:50,131
Uncle got elected!

1077
00:58:50,214 --> 00:58:52,425
What did they just say?
Did I hear that right?

1078
00:58:52,508 --> 00:58:54,010
Hooray!

1079
00:58:57,930 --> 00:58:59,974
-Was that a hallucination?
-No.

1080
00:59:00,767 --> 00:59:02,185
"Candidate 3, Park Hae-kang."

1081
00:59:02,268 --> 00:59:04,062
I'm sure I heard it too.

1082
00:59:04,145 --> 00:59:06,105
I heard it too. Park Hae-kang.

1083
00:59:06,814 --> 00:59:08,191
-Right?
-Right.

1084
00:59:08,274 --> 00:59:10,151
Does this make any sense?

1085
00:59:10,234 --> 00:59:12,445
Boss, take a look at this.

1086
00:59:14,697 --> 00:59:15,573
What is it?

1087
00:59:18,242 --> 00:59:19,327
Hello.

1088
00:59:19,410 --> 00:59:21,788
I'm Oh Sang-min,
the head of security for True Value.

1089
00:59:22,789 --> 00:59:25,541
All the guards of True Value

1090
00:59:25,625 --> 00:59:29,253
were assaulted multiple times
by the tattooed man in the video.

1091
00:59:30,296 --> 00:59:34,217
The man was assaulting
our guard Choi Su-dong,

1092
00:59:34,300 --> 00:59:36,761
who was on his shift alone that day.

1093
00:59:36,844 --> 00:59:39,055
And Mr. Park Hae-kang
was the one who helped him.

1094
00:59:39,138 --> 00:59:40,848
That lunatic picked up a shovel.

1095
00:59:42,141 --> 00:59:44,143
-Great job!
-I see.

1096
00:59:44,227 --> 00:59:45,687
-How satisfying.
-I see.

1097
00:59:45,770 --> 00:59:48,690
So that's what happened!

1098
00:59:48,773 --> 00:59:52,193
Of course, violence isn't a good thing,
but if Mr. Park hadn't helped,

1099
00:59:52,276 --> 00:59:54,320
I can't even imagine
what would have happened.

1100
00:59:54,404 --> 00:59:55,488
Kneel.

1101
00:59:55,571 --> 00:59:59,242
He seemed to be in a tight spot
because he was unfairly framed,

1102
00:59:59,325 --> 01:00:00,410
so I wanted to explain.

1103
01:00:00,493 --> 01:00:01,661
I'm sorry.

1104
01:00:02,495 --> 01:00:03,538
Apologize sincerely.

1105
01:00:04,664 --> 01:00:05,998
I'll move out right away!

1106
01:00:06,666 --> 01:00:08,292
-What?
-I'll move right away!

1107
01:00:09,001 --> 01:00:10,586
-Louder.
-I'll move right away!

1108
01:00:10,670 --> 01:00:13,673
On behalf of all the guards
of True Value State,

1109
01:00:14,549 --> 01:00:16,718
I sincerely thank Mr. Park Hae-kang.

1110
01:00:16,801 --> 01:00:17,760
The comments!

1111
01:00:17,844 --> 01:00:20,763
"I voted for Park Hae-kang
after reading this."

1112
01:00:20,847 --> 01:00:22,348
"I feel sorry I misunderstood him."

1113
01:00:22,432 --> 01:00:25,101
They're saying
you're not just a delivery hero,

1114
01:00:25,184 --> 01:00:26,477
but the hero of True Value!

1115
01:00:26,561 --> 01:00:28,146
Congratulations.

1116
01:00:28,229 --> 01:00:29,522
You've been elected.

1117
01:00:30,148 --> 01:00:32,650
Boss, congratulations on getting elected.

1118
01:00:33,276 --> 01:00:36,070
-Our boss is the building representative!
-He did it!

1119
01:00:38,656 --> 01:00:40,158
He's the building rep!

1120
01:00:42,827 --> 01:00:45,663
We did it!

1121
01:01:25,787 --> 01:01:26,871
PARK HAE-KANG MUST BE AN ANGEL

1122
01:01:26,954 --> 01:01:28,289
HE'S THE DEFINITION OF MORALLY PURE

1123
01:01:28,372 --> 01:01:29,707
I'M SO GLAD HE LIVES HERE

1124
01:01:29,791 --> 01:01:31,000
PARK HAE-KANG IS A REAL HERO!

1125
01:01:31,083 --> 01:01:32,543
ROOTING FOR YOU, PARK HAE-KANG

1126
01:01:32,627 --> 01:01:34,128
I'VE NEVER SEEN SUCH A RELIABLE CANDIDATE

1127
01:01:34,212 --> 01:01:35,922
I'D HAVE NO COMPLAINTS
IF HE WERE BUILDING REP

1128
01:01:36,005 --> 01:01:37,381
HE SURE CAN BE TRUSTED

1129
01:02:08,412 --> 01:02:10,706
THE APARTMENT JOB

1130
01:02:34,814 --> 01:02:37,316
I hear Park Hae-kang
became the building rep.

1131
01:02:37,400 --> 01:02:39,068
I found him quite interesting.

1132
01:02:39,151 --> 01:02:41,445
We all know the election
for president is coming up.

1133
01:02:41,529 --> 01:02:44,198
No one else is running, right?

1134
01:02:44,282 --> 01:02:45,408
I will run as well.

1135
01:02:46,868 --> 01:02:49,745
But I can't let him succeed
in my apartment complex.

1136
01:02:49,829 --> 01:02:51,372
-You need people on your side.
-My side?

1137
01:02:51,455 --> 01:02:54,834
Like a faction. Or a support base.

1138
01:02:54,917 --> 01:02:57,545
-Honey.
-"Honey"?

1139
01:02:57,628 --> 01:02:59,463
Elections are all about public opinion.

1140
01:02:59,547 --> 01:03:00,840
You can't defeat President Seo.

1141
01:03:00,923 --> 01:03:03,342
But President Seo,
this has to stop at just being fun.

1142
01:03:03,426 --> 01:03:04,635
You understand, don't you?

1143
01:03:04,719 --> 01:03:08,431
I heard you were the boss
of the Oasis Gang.

1144
01:03:08,514 --> 01:03:09,348
Gosh, it's hot!

1145
01:03:09,432 --> 01:03:10,641
Will this really work, though?

1146
01:03:10,725 --> 01:03:13,644
This is the only thing that can flip
public opinion about me in one shot.

1147
01:03:14,395 --> 01:03:15,897
So dig.

1148
01:03:18,566 --> 01:03:20,568
Subtitle translation by: Juyoung Park

